social_posts.post_text: Entering Sagittarius season like.. 👠 🔥

One of the most beautiful things about being human is the chance to meet other likeminded souls in this lifetime and to know them, connect with them, and to create ABUNDANT magic, bliss and memories with them. 

This fall season has treasured me with so many heart-fulfilling memories. How beautiful is it that we are able to connect, reconnect, and keep expanding in our soul journeys? 

(Wish I could share more than 10 pics, but that also reminds me the abundance of community I’ve been blessed with 🥹🙏🏼🤍)

Soul grateful 🤍🍁
Manifesting a world in which I can play a forest nymph #lenso 🌿

🌿 The most incredible year around the sun 💫

If you’re reading this, thank you so much for being in my life in some way shape or form 🙏🏼🥹

This may sound quite cheesy, but it truly has felt like everyday has been my birthday, and I am immensely grateful for all that this universe has gifted me from soul-led interactions, endless abundance, the communities I cherish so deeply, and the chance to keep doing the things I love. 🫶🏼

Can’t wait for what this new year will continue to bring!!!

What a gift life is 🤍

As Awakened Joy’s 3 yr anniversary is approaching, I have decided to conclude this chapter as a life coach, and transition towards a new path. 
 
If you knew me back in 2019, I created this program to support my mom with hospital bills, and to connect deeper with myself and others because I knew in my gut that this was my priority.  I followed my gut because I knew she would lead me towards incredible places.. and incredible places we soared indeed.🕊
 
But now, my gut is telling me to be a student of life on other passions, and I know again, I must follow what my gut is telling me. (AKA, I have to do as I preach!) 

With this, we will be pausing all in person ceremonies/retreats, monthly open circle calls and gatherings until further notice 🤍 and our Accelerator Program will be having our BIGGEST CLOSING SALE for only $333 until Jan 1st 🙏🏼 (link in bio for details) 
-
Thinking about all of the times I have cried with my clients from tears of pain to tears of celebration- being able to witness all of the WINS and all of the milestones, getting to dance, and to create absolute magic beyond what the mind could imagine- I can’t believe three years could possibly grant me something like this. This community has been everything to me. 
 
But I know that if all of this happened in just three years- I am soo ready for what AJ has in store when it comes back full force ✨
 -
If you are someone who has been wanting to participate in the Accelerator program but held back on it.. this is truly, now the only time for complete access. 
 
The entire 8 Module Accelerator available for only $333 until January 1st, 2023. This will be the biggest sale Awakened Joy has ever had (Or 10 monthly installments of $33.33)
-
And to anyone who has been a part of our calls, the AJ Accelerator program, workshops, retreats, etc. thank you, with my WHOLE heart (you know who you are!!) 😌🦋 and for being such a major part in my life.. I love you SOUL much!!!! 😭

This is not the end for AJ, but I truly believe this is just the beginning. And when I come back, it will be stronger than EVER 🤌🏽 I cannot wait for what lies ahead. 

With Love,
Ami 🤍🫶🏼✨

KOREA, you have my heart ♥️

This visit was different from all the others because I was finally able to experience the motherland on my own as an adult, seeing Korea from a whole new perspective..

6 years later and I got to be back with my roots, my grandparents and extended family, which reminded me of who I am and where I’ve come from. I’m so proud to be Korean American. I’m so proud of my culture and yearn to only learn more. Being apart from this place leaves this emptiness inside of me that I just can’t quite explain.. but I know I just need to be back here more often 🥹🫶🏼

Ten photos/videos do not do Korea justice, so get ready for a ton more to come 🥰 And to those who have been messaging me saying you now want to visit Korea, PLEASE DO!! 
I absolutely love it here!!! 🇰🇷 
(The last side of the dancing 🕺🏼 is my absolute muse)

Don’t believe everything you see on social media. 

Because what you see is only 1% of the real thing. And sometimes, the real thing is so good that no device could ever capture that feeling, those swirling emotions, that infinite moment. 💫 #unpopularopinion ?

I love capturing moments so I could look back and cherish them time and time again, but as time has went on, I realized that memory and the photos/videos taken of those moments are just different. 

Being IN the moment makes you refuse being out of it. I can take in all of my five senses and envelope each second… imprinting them into my soul, into my cells, so that my body memory cherishes them forever. 
I’ve been way more inward about what I share, and this sacred chapter just feels soul good. 

No device needed ✨

Literally Yuna and Eileen’s relationship to a T 🤣🤣🤣

“What are you so afraid of? 
There are no failures—it’s just life unfolding. Sometimes it will be miraculous, sometimes it will be mundane. Sometimes you’ll be falling in love, other times you’ll be drowning in loss. Sometimes you’ll feel high from your dreams coming true, other times you’ll feel hopeless watching them crumble. It is far better to make friends with your shadows than to run away from them. June Anthem: Rising from the Ashes 

When life pulls you towards a gravitational momentum where you just can’t look away, it’s time you go in deeper. 

So many times we are called back to the drawing board, forcing us to go deeper into our parental wounds, our traumas, our biggest fears- all because our souls are ready for it. 

I have a very strong relationship with my guides where I ask them to show me specific numbers only when they want to tell me something. And back in May, I was seeing 777 constantly left and right and I was holding my breath with a deep undertone of fear, subconsciously knowing the universe was preparing me to get ready for a lot of internal change. 

Of course, like many of us, I resist change. I don’t like it. My ego says, “I’ve already been through enough.. can’t you give me a break?!” But the universe always has higher plans, and we take it day by day. 

Becoming a student all over again and healing the mother wound, healing the father wound, letting my true self reclaim. 

Like @iamsahararose says, it’s about letting your old self die, and birthing that next version of you. Knowing you are worth it. 

I’m re-learning how to step into my power and embrace her all over again in a wholleeee new dimension cracking OPEN. And doing it for my mini me, and my future me 🥹

Anyone else rising from the ashes? 🪷🪷🪷

Every woman needs this hype song ✨

I swear, whenever I’m having a low moment, I turn to my affirmations, my mantras, my meditations, my soul lifting anthems. They get me through the hard times and the mid day train wrecks. Sometimes you’re the only one who can be your own hype woman, so you gotta find the things that you know can lift you up and sometimes even dance to. 

This is one of those moments ♥️

It’s about resetting and letting yourself dream 🪷 Creating vision boards with your sisters, disclosing some of the most vulnerable truths that may be too scary to say but you do so anyway 

Sleeping in on a Saturday night at 8 
just because, and waking up with the sun, wondering what abundance awaits 🧿

It’s about spending quality time - without phones in hand- looking eye to eye, basking in the awe of their magnificent presence, this moment: only here and now 

Taking this sweet serenity of fresh figs and plump green grapes out in summers day 

licking your lips-getting-your-hands-dirty rolling around in the grass kind of play

Utilizing all your five senses 

Stop and smell the roses 🌹
Found myself in lavender field heaven 💜🪻🩵

Been embracing the softer moments, the quiet hues. Many of us are so used to overdoing, overworking, hustling and grinding till we’re exhausted, and now I’m in a place where I’m finally understanding why deep rest is important. Doing nothing is actually everything (!!!!!) There’s nothing lazy about it 🙏🏼 Resetting my nervous system to feeling peace and calm rather than constant chaos and anxiety (survival mode). Why my soul going through “her winter” is a celebration itself because she feels safe to do so. 

Have you also been in a similar season? It’s been such an illuminating shift 🧚🏼‍♂️🪷🧿😌
Creating my own Barbie world 😛🫦🛼😍👠🌸🪱 #tantrafitness

I wonder what life is like in full bloom, where peace is my resounding constant -

And I’m no longer chasing that expansive feeling 

Knowing that peace is my truth, 
and the expansion is me. 🕊️

5 ways to Romanticize your life ✨

1. Listen to music that makes you feel good 
2. Relish in nourishing foods that draw in your taste buds
3. Look at colors that brighten your soul 🧡 💛 
4. Put on a candle or diffuser to calm your mind 
5. Hug your loved ones, hug yourself, cozy up in warm blankets and embrace your furry animals 

Also- whether it’s a form of singing, dancing, acting, being with nature, etc. giving myself permission to soften + play has been so important. Maybe the fall cozy season is hunkering me down into this muse, but it’s been reminding me that we are deserving of play in every way. 

 For those of you who are also working on shedding that consistent grind mindset and sometimes feeling as though “having fun has to be earned,”

I hope this is a gentle reminder that romanticizing our lives comes at no extra cost ✨ 

🧡 Tag a friend who needs this reminder :)

This birthday hits different 💐 ..

All I wanted for my birthday is to be with my mom. I’m so grateful for her. I wouldn’t be here without her. I’m cherishing the little moments I so wanted to skip when I was younger because I kept striving for only the BIG ones. 

But I’m now realizing that wasn’t really me.. that was just the survival in me trying to impress my family so that we were all assimilating and becoming more accepted into this western culture. 

But now I yearn to lean into my Korean roots 🇰🇷 
To know what it’s like to speak my native tongue more than I do English. To cook Korean food and learn about all of the different types of herbs and all of their medicinal qualities. I want to meet my 101 year old great grandmother who ran her farm for decades and learn how to grow and ferment different Korean crops from her. 

So many things I crave to do and be 😌🙏🏼

This year has taught me to not play small. 
To CHOOSE myself. To put my intuition above all. I’ve learned how to be comfortable with the WHOLE of me. Not just a few versions, but becoming deep lovers with all parts of who I am, and who I am becoming. 

I yearn to continue my growth, to be a student, and to ferociously forge my path to be all of who I am meant to be. 
 
If you’ve been reading this far, thank you, from the bottom of my heart for witnessing me in all of the ever changing, various stages of Ami 🩵✨ 

I am so grateful.
